## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- pnpm or npm
- MongoDB Atlas account (free tier works)
- Google Gemini API key (free at https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey)

## Quick Start

### 1. Clone and install

```bash
# Backend
cd backend
npm install

# Frontend
cd ../frontend
npm install
```

### 2. Configure environment variables

**Backend** — copy `backend/.env.example` to `backend/.env` and fill in:

```env
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=5000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@<cluster>.mongodb.net/intellmeet
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-key-min-32-chars
JWT_EXPIRE=7d
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
```

**Frontend** — copy `frontend/.env.example` to `frontend/.env`:

```env
VITE_API_URL=/api
VITE_SOCKET_URL=
```

The Vite dev server proxies `/api` to `http://localhost:5000` automatically.

### 3. Start both servers

```bash
# Terminal 1 — Backend
cd backend
npm run dev

# Terminal 2 — Frontend
cd frontend
npm run dev
```

Open http://localhost:5173

## API Routes

### Auth
| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| POST | /api/auth/register | Register new user |
| POST | /api/auth/login | Login |
| GET | /api/auth/me | Get current user |
| PUT | /api/auth/me | Update profile |

### Meetings
| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| GET | /api/meetings | List all meetings |
| POST | /api/meetings | Create meeting |
| GET | /api/meetings/:id | Get meeting detail |
| PUT | /api/meetings/:id | Update meeting |
| DELETE | /api/meetings/:id | Delete meeting |
| POST | /api/meetings/:id/start | Start meeting |
| POST | /api/meetings/:id/end | End meeting |
| GET | /api/meetings/upcoming | Upcoming scheduled meetings |
| GET | /api/meetings/recent | Recently ended meetings |

### AI (Gemini)
| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| POST | /api/ai/meetings/:id/summary | Generate AI summary |
| GET | /api/ai/meetings/:id/summary | Get saved summary |
| POST | /api/ai/meetings/:id/extract-actions | Extract action items with AI |
| POST | /api/ai/meetings/:id/transcript | Add transcript entry |
| GET | /api/ai/meetings/:id/transcript | Get full transcript |

### Action Items
| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| GET | /api/tasks | List tasks (filterable) |
| POST | /api/tasks | Create task |
| PUT | /api/tasks/:id | Update task |
| DELETE | /api/tasks/:id | Delete task |
| GET | /api/tasks/stats | Task statistics |

### Analytics
| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| GET | /api/analytics/dashboard | Full dashboard stats |
| GET | /api/analytics/meetings | Meetings over time (chart data) |
| GET | /api/analytics/action-items | Action item breakdown |

## Socket.io Events

### Client → Server
| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `join_meeting` | `{ meetingId }` | Join a meeting room |
| `leave_meeting` | `{ meetingId }` | Leave a meeting room |
| `send_message` | `{ meetingId, content }` | Send a chat message |
| `toggle_media` | `{ meetingId, isMuted, isVideoOn }` | Broadcast media state |

### Server → Client
| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `recent_messages` | `Message[]` | Messages on join |
| `new_message` | `Message` | New chat message |
| `user_joined` | `{ userId, name }` | A participant joined |
| `user_left` | `{ userId, name }` | A participant left |
| `meeting_started` | `{ meetingId }` | Meeting went live |
| `meeting_ended` | `{ meetingId }` | Meeting ended |
| `participant_media_update` | `{ userId, isMuted, isVideoOn }` | Media toggle update |

## Production Deployment

### Backend (e.g. Railway, Render, Fly.io)

1. Set all env vars from `.env.example`
2. Set `NODE_ENV=production`
3. Start command: `node server.js`

### Frontend (e.g. Vercel, Netlify)

1. Build: `npm run build`
2. Serve: `dist/` directory
3. Set `VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.railway.app/api`
4. Set `VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://your-api.railway.app`
5. Add rewrite rule: `/*` → `/index.html` (SPA routing)

### CORS

Update `CLIENT_URL` in the backend `.env` to your frontend production URL.

